candidate for any of the armed services?  I have.  I've taken both the Navy and the Air Force's aptitude tests and scored in the 90th percentile on both( a 9/9 on the general and aviation portion of the Navy's test).  Bush's scores might have gotten him command of a fuel truck, they certainly wouldn't have gotten him a flight slot. You need to score in the top quartile, not the bottom to be selected.<br>
<br>
Bush's scores?  General 98th percentile, Pilot 25th percentile, Navigator 50th percentile.<br>
<br>
At the time Bush was admitted to the national guard, there was a year and a half waiting list for admission. Bush was admitted to his unit the day he enlisted.  Buck Staudt even re-administered the oath to bush in Public so that there would be a photo opp.<br>
<br>
Here's the chain of contacts: George HW Bush to Sid Adger  (local oil magnate) to Texas Speaker of the House Ben Jarnes to General James Rose, the head of the Texas Air National Guard.  Rose, who is now dead, told his friend and former legislator Jake Johnson that &quot;I got that Republican congressman's son from Houston into the Guard.&quot;<br>
<br>
Bush was also approved for direct appointment, despite zero ROTC experience, the lack of technical or medical skills, or prior flight training.  Sooo, he didn't have to go to officer candidate school like everyone else.  Direct appointments, for you non-military  folks, usually go to physicians and nurses, who get a couple of weeks of &quot;knife and fork school.&quot;<br>
<br>
Buck Staudt scheduled another press-publicized photo opp for Bush's direct appointment.<br>
<br>
And the composition of Bush's unit?  That was coincidence?  A commander of a unit filled with the sons of political leaders and sports figures says that his daddy didn't do anything for him?  And none of the other daddy's did anything for their own sons either?  They all, just by happy circumstance and alignment of the planets ended up in a non-combat unit close to home?  <br>
<br>
Believe in Santa Claus too? <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://p075.ezboard.com/bascension10244.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bumraz@ascension10244>Bumraz</A> at: 6/8/04 5:23 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p075.ezboard.com/bascension10244.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kurakaikhan>Kurakai Khan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Daddy</span><br>  Posts: 490<br> <font color=#333333>(6/8/04 5:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://p075.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2705.topic&index=83>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> So what you are saying is you have no facts to refute what the commander of his own unit said, the fact that he received an honorable discharge and the fact that no draft was dodged seeing as how he wasn't drafted due to the fact that he was ALREADY in the military, just allegations and your own test results as evidence.<br>
